Run:

1) run server:
./server

It only creates a "server.ior" file.

2) run client:

./client

It will read IOR from server.ior, start 2 threads and 2 timers in ORB's reactor.

timer1 fires after 2 sec, and sleeps for 10 seconds.
timer2 fires after 3 sec, and tries to contact the server using server.ior

instead of reporting CORBA::TRANSIENT, it reports CORBA::TIMEOUT.

